t: To the chief Musician on Neginoth, Maschil, A Psalm of David, when the Ziphites came and said to Saul, Doth not David hide himself with us?
Save*p me, O God, by thy name, and judge me by thy strength.
Hear*p my prayer, O God; give ear to the words of my mouth.
For*p strangers are risen up against me, and oppressors seek after my soul: they have not set God before them. Selah.
Behold,*p God is mine helper: the Lord is with them that uphold my soul.
He*p shall reward evil unto mine enemies: cut them off in thy truth.
I*p will freely sacrifice unto thee: I will praise thy name, O Lord;*s for it is good.
For*p he hath delivered me out of all trouble: and mine eye hath seen his desire upon mine enemies.
